WEBVTT

00:17.718 --> 00:20.221
(woman)
WHEN I WAS A LITTLE GIRL,

00:20.221 --> 00:22.053
MY UNDERSTANDING OF REVENGE

00:22.053 --> 00:24.355
WAS AS SIMPLE
AS THE SUNDAY SCHOOL PROVERBS

00:24.355 --> 00:26.597
IT HID BEHIND.

00:28.129 --> 00:30.561
NEAT LITTLE MORALITY SLOGANS,

00:30.561 --> 00:33.134
LIKE "DO UNTO OTHERS"

00:33.134 --> 00:35.506
AND "TWO WRONGS
DON'T MAKE A RIGHT."

00:35.506 --> 00:37.438
(gunshot)

00:37.438 --> 00:41.672
(Angus & Julia Stone)
♪ IF YOU LOVE ME ♪

00:41.672 --> 00:43.043
(fireworks
popping and whistling)

00:43.043 --> 00:45.616
BUT TWO WRONGS
CAN NEVER MAKE A RIGHT

00:45.616 --> 00:48.679
BECAUSE TWO WRONGS
CAN NEVER EQUAL EACH OTHER.

00:48.679 --> 00:51.682
(whistling and popping
continues)

00:51.682 --> 00:54.685
(dance music playing faintly)

00:54.685 --> 00:57.328
(people speaking indistinctly)

00:59.230 --> 01:01.792
(indistinct conversations)

01:01.792 --> 01:04.135
♪♪♪

01:04.135 --> 01:05.596
(speaks indistinctly)

01:05.596 --> 01:08.068
FOR THE TRULY WRONGED...

01:08.068 --> 01:10.601
REAL SATISFACTION
CAN ONLY BE FOUND

01:10.601 --> 01:13.144
IN ONE OF TWO PLACES...

01:13.144 --> 01:16.147
ABSOLUTE FORGIVENESS...

01:16.147 --> 01:18.409
OR MORTAL VINDICATION.

01:18.409 --> 01:20.211
♪♪♪

01:20.211 --> 01:23.384
THIS ISNOTA STORY
ABOUT FORGIVENESS.

01:23.384 --> 01:25.456
(woman, British accent)
EMILY.

01:25.456 --> 01:27.118
♪♪♪

01:27.118 --> 01:29.820
I'VE BEEN LOOKING FOR YOU.
WHERE'S DANIEL?

01:29.820 --> 01:33.124
UH, HE'S WALKING THE BEACH.
WE'RE HAVING A THING.

01:33.124 --> 01:34.695
SAME THING
OR DIFFERENT THING?

01:34.695 --> 01:37.168
SAME THING. BUT DON'T WORRY.
HE'S RIGHT BEHIND ME.

01:37.168 --> 01:40.131
IT'S MY JOB TO WORRY.
YOUR JOB IS TO ENJOY YOURSELF.

01:40.131 --> 01:42.703
IT'S YOUR ENGAGEMENT PARTY.

01:42.703 --> 01:45.406
CAN SOMEONE GET ME A 20
ON DANIEL GRAYSON?

01:45.406 --> 01:46.477
HEY, CONGRATS, EMILY.

01:46.477 --> 01:47.708
THANK YOU.

01:47.708 --> 01:49.410
(indistinct conversations)

01:49.410 --> 01:52.213
♪♪♪

01:52.213 --> 01:54.285
NICE NIGHT FOR IT.

01:54.285 --> 01:56.317
NICE NIGHT FOR WHAT,
NOLAN?

01:56.317 --> 01:59.250
CELEBRATING.

01:59.250 --> 02:01.392
YOU SHOULDN'T BE HERE.

02:01.392 --> 02:03.624
THAT MAKES TWO OF US.

02:03.624 --> 02:06.126
(woman) EMILY,
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN HIDING?

02:06.126 --> 02:08.127
(woman) COME ON.
LET'S SEE THAT RING, GIRL.

02:08.127 --> 02:10.161
(Emily) HI.

02:10.161 --> 02:11.662
(indistinct conversations
continue)

02:14.465 --> 02:17.468
(grunting)

02:20.171 --> 02:22.673
(panting)

02:22.673 --> 02:25.176
(grunts)

02:25.176 --> 02:29.420
♪♪♪

02:29.420 --> 02:32.653
(indistinct conversations)

02:32.653 --> 02:35.286
(laughs)

02:35.286 --> 02:37.328
I FEEL LIKE A JACKASS
IN THIS TUX.

02:37.328 --> 02:38.829
WELL, STOP ACTING LIKE ONE,

02:38.829 --> 02:40.331
AND YOU'LL STOP
FEELING LIKE ONE.

02:40.331 --> 02:42.833
TRUST ME. IF YOUR FRIENDS
COULD SEE YOU NOW--

02:42.833 --> 02:44.335
I'D PROBABLY GET JUMPED.

02:44.335 --> 02:45.496
MM.

02:45.496 --> 02:47.468
♪♪♪

02:47.468 --> 02:50.170
HEY, YOU REALLY WANT
OUTTA THAT TUX?

02:50.170 --> 02:53.173
(indistinct conversations
continue)

02:53.173 --> 02:54.445
♪♪♪

02:57.778 --> 02:59.250
(thud)

02:59.250 --> 03:00.851
(music playing faintly)

03:00.851 --> 03:02.313
(voices murmuring faintly)

03:02.313 --> 03:04.315
COME ON.
WE'LL RUN AWAY TOGETHER.

03:04.315 --> 03:05.286
YOU'RE SLOW.

03:05.286 --> 03:07.187
(laughs)
I'M GOING. I'M GOING.

03:07.187 --> 03:08.559
LITTLE TOO MUCH FOOD
LATELY.

03:08.559 --> 03:10.521
(laughing) COME ON.
 MAYBE NOT.

03:10.521 --> 03:13.594
(girl laughs)

03:13.594 --> 03:15.226
(boy)
WHERE ARE WE GOING?

03:15.226 --> 03:17.298
(laughs) YOU ASK
TOO MANY QUESTIONS.

03:17.298 --> 03:20.501
(laughs) SHOW ME
WHAT YOU GOT, BAD BOY.

03:20.501 --> 03:22.303
HERE. LET ME HELP YOU.

03:22.303 --> 03:23.934
I GOT IT. I GOT IT.

03:23.934 --> 03:25.306
(speaks indistinctly)

03:25.306 --> 03:26.537
(speaks indistinctly)

03:29.310 --> 03:31.342
FIRE AND ICE...

03:31.342 --> 03:34.985
WHEN WE FIRST SAT DOWN
TO DISCUSS TONIGHT'S OCCASION,

03:34.985 --> 03:37.288
I WAS IMMEDIATELY TAKEN
WITH THE IDEA

03:37.288 --> 03:40.851
OF AN EVENING INSPIRED
BY PRIMAL BOOKENDS--

03:40.851 --> 03:42.493
FIRE AND ICE...

03:42.493 --> 03:45.826
BEGINNINGS AND ENDINGS...

03:45.826 --> 03:48.999
AND THE LOVE BETWEEN
A MAN AND A WOMAN.

03:48.999 --> 03:50.801
(applause)

03:50.801 --> 03:52.563
(phone rings)

03:52.563 --> 03:54.665
(applause continues)

03:54.665 --> 03:57.237
(cell phone rings)

03:58.909 --> 03:59.910
(ring)

03:59.910 --> 04:01.742
YO. YO, 8 MILE,

04:01.742 --> 04:04.345
PRIVATE PARTY HERE!
 (ring)

04:04.345 --> 04:06.347
(woman speaking indistinctly,
amplified voice)

04:06.347 --> 04:07.878
(woman)
...A STARRY EVENING.
 (phone rings)

04:07.878 --> 04:10.321
THAT CREEP BETTER NOT
BE TAKING PICTURES.

04:10.321 --> 04:12.553
(cell phone rings)

04:12.553 --> 04:13.754
HEY!

04:13.754 --> 04:16.387
(ring)
 YOU GOT A PROBLEM?!

04:16.387 --> 04:19.829
(woman continues speaking
indistinctly, amplified voice)

04:19.829 --> 04:22.593
(ring)
 TONIGHT NOT ONLY MARKS
THE FINAL WEEKEND

04:22.593 --> 04:24.865
OF A REMARKABLE SUMMER
IN THE HAMPTONS,

04:24.865 --> 04:26.837
IT IS ALSO THE CELEBRATION

04:26.837 --> 04:29.400
OF MY SON DANIEL'S ENGAGEMENT...
 (ringing)

04:29.400 --> 04:30.941
TO THE LOVELY AND BEGUILING

04:30.941 --> 04:33.374
MS. EMILY THORNE.

04:33.374 --> 04:35.676
(indistinct shouting)

04:35.676 --> 04:36.877
(applause)

04:36.877 --> 04:38.879
AND THOUGH WE'VE ONLY KNOWN HER

04:38.879 --> 04:40.381
FOR A FEW SHORT MONTHS,

04:40.381 --> 04:44.054
EMILY ALREADY FEELS LIKE
THE PIECE OF THE FAMILY PUZZLE

04:44.054 --> 04:46.317
WE NEVER EVEN KNEW
WAS MISSING.

04:46.317 --> 04:48.319
(guests) AW.

04:48.319 --> 04:49.360
IN A WORD,

04:49.360 --> 04:51.592
I APPROVE.

04:51.592 --> 04:54.465
(chuckles)
AND AS ANYONE CAN TELL YOU,

04:54.465 --> 04:57.728
APPROVAL IS NOT SOMETHING
I GIVE AWAY FREELY.

04:57.728 --> 05:00.771
(all laugh)

05:00.771 --> 05:02.773
WHERE THE HELL
IS MY SON?

05:02.773 --> 05:05.736
(indistinct conversations)

05:11.682 --> 05:14.314
CHARLOTTE.

05:16.046 --> 05:17.888
OH, MY GOD.

05:17.888 --> 05:19.950
(gasps)

05:23.053 --> 05:25.956
MOM!

05:25.956 --> 05:27.358
MOM!

05:27.358 --> 05:29.329
MOM!

05:29.329 --> 05:31.732
MY BROTHER...
SOMEBODY COME HERE!

05:31.732 --> 05:33.664
(guests speaking indistinctly)

05:33.664 --> 05:35.406
(Charlotte) COME HERE!

05:35.406 --> 05:37.868
MOM!

05:37.868 --> 05:40.340
DANIEL!

05:45.476 --> 05:48.519
(woman) DANIEL!

05:48.519 --> 05:49.480
DANIEL!

05:49.480 --> 05:52.383
GET AWAY FROM MY SON!

05:52.383 --> 05:54.585
DANIEL!

05:54.585 --> 05:59.390
DANIEL, PLEASE!
(crying) NO!

05:59.390 --> 06:02.092
DANIEL!

06:02.092 --> 06:04.134
(woman) I CAN'T TELL YOU
WHAT A RARE OPPORTUNITY

06:04.134 --> 06:06.136
YOU HAVE HERE, MS. THORNE.

06:06.136 --> 06:08.138
THE CURRENT OWNERS LIVE
IN THE CITY, OF COURSE,

06:08.138 --> 06:11.371
BUT THEY'VE BEEN
LOYAL HAMPTONITES FOR YEARS.

06:11.371 --> 06:14.575
PERHAPS IF MR. DAVIS HAD BEEN
A BIT MORE LOYAL TO HIS WIFE,

06:14.575 --> 06:17.448
THEY WOULDN'T BE RENTING OUT
THIS SEASON.

06:17.448 --> 06:19.109
WORD HAS IT, HE DUMPED HER

06:19.109 --> 06:21.812
FOR A GIRL HALF HIS AGE.
(chuckles)

06:21.812 --> 06:24.485
MEN.

06:24.485 --> 06:26.386
YOU MIND IF I LOOK AROUND
A BIT?

06:26.386 --> 06:27.558
(sets picture down)

06:27.558 --> 06:29.760
THAT'S WHAT WE'RE HERE FOR.

06:29.760 --> 06:31.161
(door opens)

06:31.161 --> 06:34.695
(wind chimes tinkling)

06:36.497 --> 06:40.100
(gulls crying)

06:40.100 --> 06:41.902
(door closes)

06:53.984 --> 06:57.518
♪ HERE I GO ♪

06:57.518 --> 06:58.889
(girl) DAD?

06:58.889 --> 07:00.721
♪ I'LL TELL YOU ♪

07:00.721 --> 07:02.753
HEY, KIDDO.
YOU HAVING FUN EXPLORING?

07:02.753 --> 07:05.556
WE REALLY GET TO SPEND
THE WHOLE SUMMER HERE?

07:05.556 --> 07:07.097
AND EVERY SUMMER
AFTER THAT.

07:07.097 --> 07:09.730
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

07:09.730 --> 07:11.632
I THINK
MOM WOULD'VE LOVED IT.

07:13.063 --> 07:17.437
HEY, YOU KNOW HOW MUCH
I LOVE YOU, AMANDA?

07:17.437 --> 07:18.809
INFINITY?

07:18.809 --> 07:22.513
WELL, INFINITY...

07:22.513 --> 07:24.975
♪ WITH ALL OF YOUR HEART ♪

07:24.975 --> 07:27.678
TIMES INFINITY.

07:30.080 --> 07:32.452
♪ IF YOU LOVE ME ♪

07:32.452 --> 07:34.154
(door opens)
 MS. THORNE?

07:34.154 --> 07:35.756
NOW YOU HAVE TO IMAGINE,

07:35.756 --> 07:37.858
IT'S MEMORIAL DAY WEEKEND,

07:37.858 --> 07:39.690
75 AND SUNNY,

07:39.690 --> 07:43.634
ALL THOSE BOYS OF SUMMER
WONDERING WHO THE NEW GIRL IS.

07:43.634 --> 07:45.696
AND THAT'S GRAYSON MANOR.

07:45.696 --> 07:49.169
YOU WON'T FIND
A BETTER ADDRESS THAN THIS.

07:49.169 --> 07:51.171
I'LL TAKE IT.

07:51.171 --> 07:53.003
OH. WONDERFUL.

07:53.003 --> 07:54.505
I'LL GET THE CONTRACT.

07:54.505 --> 07:57.678
♪ SHINING YOUR LIGHT ♪

07:57.678 --> 08:00.851
♪ MY WAY ♪

08:08.689 --> 08:11.261
(man) ♪ SAY LA, LA, LA,
LA, LA, LA, LA, LA ♪

08:11.261 --> 08:13.824
♪ SAY LA, LA, LA,
LA, LA, LA, LA, LA ♪

08:13.824 --> 08:15.225
(knock on door)

08:15.225 --> 08:16.697
HELLO, HELLO.

08:16.697 --> 08:17.868
ASHLEY, HEY.

08:17.868 --> 08:19.530
HEY.

08:19.530 --> 08:21.131
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

08:21.131 --> 08:23.133
ARE YOU KIDDING?
LOOK AT THIS PLACE.

08:23.133 --> 08:24.504
I WANT YOUR LIFE.

08:24.504 --> 08:25.636
YOU LOVE YOUR LIFE.

08:25.636 --> 08:27.137
YEAH, YOU'RE RIGHT.
I JUST WANT YOUR MONEY.

08:27.137 --> 08:29.239
WHAT'S MINE IS YOURS.
SHOULD I GET US SOME GLASSES?

08:29.239 --> 08:31.682
I WISH.
IT'S FOR VICTORIA GRAYSON.

08:31.682 --> 08:33.544
WHO?
 YOU ARE HOPELESS.

08:33.544 --> 08:35.546
VICTORIA GRAYSON--

08:35.546 --> 08:37.548
REIGNING QUEEN
OF THE HAMPTONS.

08:37.548 --> 08:40.289
NOT TO MENTION,
YOUR NEW NEXT DOOR NEIGHBOR.

08:40.289 --> 08:42.553
QUEEN VICTORIA?

08:42.553 --> 08:44.054
MM. BELIEVE ME,
SHE'S EARNED THE TITLE.

08:44.054 --> 08:45.756
MY BOSS HAS ME HANDLING
THE GUEST LIST

08:45.756 --> 08:47.527
FOR HER MEMORIAL DAY PARTY.

08:47.527 --> 08:49.560
MM.

08:49.560 --> 08:51.702
IF I SCREW THIS UP, I MIGHT
AS WELL MOVE BACK TO CROYDON.

08:51.702 --> 08:53.533
WELL, HOW MUCH
ARE THE TICKETS?

08:53.533 --> 08:54.835
10,000 A POP.

08:54.835 --> 08:56.536
COUNT ME IN FOR ONE.

08:56.536 --> 08:57.908
ARE YOU SURE?

08:57.908 --> 08:59.309
IT'S FOR A GOOD CAUSE,
RIGHT?

08:59.309 --> 09:01.912
YEAH, MY CAREER.
THANK YOU.

09:01.912 --> 09:05.576
YOU WANT TO GET DRUNK
ON CHEAP MARGARITAS LATER?

09:05.576 --> 09:06.917
WITH OR WITHOUT YOU.

09:06.917 --> 09:08.679
GOOD LUCK WITH HER HIGHNESS.

09:08.679 --> 09:10.921
BYE.

09:16.627 --> 09:19.630
(wind chimes tinkling)

09:28.669 --> 09:31.571
LET'S DUMP OUR LONG POSITION
ON 5- AND 10-YEAR TREASURIES

09:31.571 --> 09:33.573
BEFORE THE FED
STOPS BUYING THEM UP.

09:33.573 --> 09:36.276
AND, UH, GET US INTO SOME OF
THOSE LOW-RATED TECH BONDS.

09:36.276 --> 09:37.948
THANKS.

09:37.948 --> 09:39.710
LOOKS LIKE LYDIA AND MICHAEL'S
NEW RENTER IS SETTLING IN.

09:39.710 --> 09:41.782
(cell phone beeps)
 LUCKY GIRL,
SCORING THAT PROPERTY.

09:41.782 --> 09:43.283
PRETTY ONE, TOO,

09:43.283 --> 09:44.715
EVEN FROM UP HERE.

09:44.715 --> 09:47.618
I GUESS THAT MAKES HER
DOUBLY LUCKY.

09:47.618 --> 09:49.159
I DON'T BELIEVE IN LUCK.

09:49.159 --> 09:51.161
I THOUGHT YOU WERE TAKING
THE WEEKEND OFF.

09:51.161 --> 09:52.663
(tv playing indistinctly)

09:52.663 --> 09:55.095
(clicks)
 THERE. I'M OFF.

09:55.095 --> 09:56.196
MM.

09:56.196 --> 09:57.928
HEY.

09:57.928 --> 10:00.330
EW. GET A ROOM,
YOU GUYS.

10:00.330 --> 10:03.273
OH, I'M SORRY, CHARLIE.
I DIDN'T SEE YOU SNEAKING IN.

10:03.273 --> 10:05.836
DIDN'T SEE YOU SNEAKING OUT
LAST NIGHT, EITHER, CHARLOTTE.

10:05.836 --> 10:08.008
I WENT OVER TO TRACEY'S.

10:08.008 --> 10:10.340
TOLD YOU I WAS GOING
BEFORE YOU WENT TO BED.
 NO, YOU DIDN'T.

10:10.340 --> 10:11.942
MOM, YOU'RE TOO YOUNG AND TOO
PRETTY TO BE THIS SENILE.

10:11.942 --> 10:13.383
HMM.

10:13.383 --> 10:15.185
(tv continues playing
indistinctly)

10:15.185 --> 10:17.818
REMIND ME TO BUY HER
A CAT BELL.

10:17.818 --> 10:19.950
AW, LET HER HAVE
A LITTLE FUN.

10:19.950 --> 10:22.122
SHE GOT STRAIGHT A's
THIS YEAR.

10:22.122 --> 10:24.194
NO ONE'S ACCUSING HER
OF BEING STUPID.

10:24.194 --> 10:26.256
♪♪♪

10:26.256 --> 10:29.700
(people speaking indistinctly)

10:29.700 --> 10:32.032
DON'T THINK
I DIDN'T SEE YOU EYEBALLING

10:32.032 --> 10:34.304
THAT CASE OF BEER, DEC.
 OUR DAD OWNS A BAR, DUMBASS.

10:34.304 --> 10:35.666
I CAN GET AS MUCH BEER
AS I WANT.

10:35.666 --> 10:37.107
ALL RIGHT.
WELL, IN THAT CASE,

10:37.107 --> 10:39.109
I'LL JUST HAVE TO MAKE SURE
DAD DOUBLE-CHECKS THE INVENTORY

10:39.109 --> 10:40.971
WHILE I'M GONE.
 UH-HUH. YEAH.

10:40.971 --> 10:42.873
WHY DON'T YOU TELL ME
ANOTHER HUNDRED TIMES, HUH?

10:42.873 --> 10:44.715
DID YOU ALREADY WASH
THOSE GARBAGE BINS OUT BACK?

10:44.715 --> 10:46.977
BEATS UPLOADING
THIS FUTURE SHIPWRECK.

10:46.977 --> 10:48.979
♪♪♪

10:48.979 --> 10:51.421
AHOY! CAPTAIN PORTER.

10:51.421 --> 10:53.653
(chuckles)

10:53.653 --> 10:55.926
WELCOME BACK, NOLAN.
WHAT CAN I DO FOR YOU?

10:55.926 --> 10:58.258
NEED A BOAT FOR THE SUMMER.

10:58.258 --> 11:00.761
THIS ONE WILL DO.

11:00.761 --> 11:02.763
IT'S NOT FOR RENT.

11:02.763 --> 11:04.364
WHO SAID ANYTHING
ABOUT RENTING?

11:04.364 --> 11:06.236
HOW MUCH YOU WANT FOR...

11:06.236 --> 11:08.298
"AMANDA"?

11:08.298 --> 11:10.070
IT'S NOT FOR SALE, EITHER.

11:10.070 --> 11:11.671
♪♪♪

11:11.671 --> 11:14.244
I'M TAKING IT DOWN TO HAITI
NEXT WEEK.

11:14.244 --> 11:16.146
I THOUGHT YOU HATED
THE OCEAN.

11:16.146 --> 11:18.408
WELL, I-I SPENT A LOT OF TIME
AND MONEY

11:18.408 --> 11:20.751
WORKING THROUGH THAT,
AMONGST OTHER THINGS.

11:20.751 --> 11:22.412
SO...

11:22.412 --> 11:24.885
I'M BUYING A BOAT.

11:24.885 --> 11:26.086
RIGHT.

11:26.086 --> 11:27.818
JUST NOT THIS ONE.

11:27.818 --> 11:29.920
(people speaking indistinctly)

11:29.920 --> 11:31.922
AMANDA MUST BE
SOME SPECIAL GIRL.

11:31.922 --> 11:33.794
CAN I HELP YOU
WITH SOMETHING?

11:33.794 --> 11:35.425
YOU DON'T LIKE ME MUCH,

11:35.425 --> 11:37.728
DO YOU?

11:37.728 --> 11:39.930
ONE MORE THING FOR YOU
TO WORK THROUGH, I GUESS.

11:39.930 --> 11:43.033
(people continue
speaking indistinctly)

11:43.033 --> 11:45.135
♪♪♪

11:45.135 --> 11:46.737
(Ashley)
THE RESPONSE TO YOUR

11:46.737 --> 11:48.779
"IN WITH THE NEW"
MEMORIAL DAY PARTY

11:48.779 --> 11:50.110
HAS BEEN OVERWHELMING,
MRS. GRAYSON.

11:50.110 --> 11:52.012
THE PARTY IS AT 90% CAPACITY...

11:52.012 --> 11:53.443
(women murmuring)

11:53.443 --> 11:54.945
AND THE "REGRETS" WEB SITE'S

11:54.945 --> 11:57.317
ALREADY COLLECTED
NEARLY $50,000,

11:57.317 --> 11:59.750
FOR EVERYTHING FROM
DOMESTIC VIOLENCE PREVENTION

11:59.750 --> 12:01.051
TO CANCER AWARENESS.

12:01.051 --> 12:02.392
SOME OF THESE REGRETS

12:02.392 --> 12:04.424
WOULDN'T WIPE THEIR NOSES
WITH $50,000, DEAR.

12:04.424 --> 12:05.926
(women chuckle)

12:05.926 --> 12:07.928
IF WE'RE GOING TO SET A MORE
GENEROUS TONE FOR THE SUMMER,

12:07.928 --> 12:09.459
IT'S CLEAR I'M GOING TO
HAVE TO DO SOMETHING FRESH

12:09.459 --> 12:11.231
AND PROVOCATIVE, SO...

12:11.231 --> 12:12.732
I'VE DECIDED
TO AUCTION OFF A PIECE

12:12.732 --> 12:14.504
FROM MY PERSONAL ART COLLECTION.

12:14.504 --> 12:16.266
WHAT A WILD IDEA,
VICTORIA.

12:16.266 --> 12:18.468
WELL, I DON'T CARE
HOW GOOD THE CAUSE IS,

12:18.468 --> 12:20.410
IF YOU PUT UP THE van GOGH
THAT MICHAEL AND I GAVE YOU...

12:20.410 --> 12:22.412
(chuckles)
I'LL KILL MYSELF.

12:22.412 --> 12:24.514
THE van GOGH IS OFF LIMITS
FOR SENTIMENTAL REASONS.

12:24.514 --> 12:26.446
PLEASE.
 (sighs) OKAY.

12:26.446 --> 12:29.019
ASHLEY, WOULD YOU PLEASE ADD
THE NEW ANNOUNCEMENT

12:29.019 --> 12:31.782
TO THE WEB SITE, SEE IF WE CAN'T
DRUM UP SOME MORE BUSINESS?

12:31.782 --> 12:33.523
AND, LADIES, THANKS AGAIN.
 (women speak indistinctly)

12:33.523 --> 12:35.525
LYDIA...

12:35.525 --> 12:37.057
WE WERE ALL SO SORRY

12:37.057 --> 12:38.929
TO HEAR ABOUT YOU AND MICHAEL
THIS WINTER.

12:38.929 --> 12:40.831
YOU WERE ONE OF THOSE COUPLES
EVERYONE ROOTS FOR.

12:40.831 --> 12:42.762
I HAVE NO DOUBT.

12:42.762 --> 12:45.936
(women speaking indistinctly)

12:45.936 --> 12:47.998
HOW ARE YOU HOLDING UP?

12:47.998 --> 12:50.841
MICHAEL'S THREATENING TO PUT
THE BEACH HOUSE ON THE MARKET

12:50.841 --> 12:53.773
IF I DON'T RELEASE MY CLAIM
ON THE WEST SIDE WALK-UP.

12:53.773 --> 12:56.246
IT'S BAD ENOUGH, HAVING
SOME STRANGER RENTING IT OUT.

12:56.246 --> 12:58.048
I CAN'T BEAR THE THOUGHT
OF LOSING IT

12:58.048 --> 13:00.050
TO ONE OF THE SHE-WOLVES.

13:00.050 --> 13:02.813
MM. WELL, THEN DON'T LET THEM
SEE YOUR WEAKNESS.

13:02.813 --> 13:04.554
IT'S THE FIRST THING
THEY'LL USE AGAINST YOU.

13:04.554 --> 13:06.516
(women continue speaking
indistinctly)

13:06.516 --> 13:07.557
ALL RIGHT?

13:07.557 --> 13:09.559
MM-HMM. THANK YOU.

13:09.559 --> 13:11.161
(sighs)

13:11.161 --> 13:12.562
(sighs)

13:12.562 --> 13:15.565
(indistinct conversations)

13:15.565 --> 13:18.999
(Angus & Julia Stone's "Hold On"
playing)

13:18.999 --> 13:22.002
(indistinct conversations
continue)

13:27.337 --> 13:30.981
♪ AND I'M WAITING FOR THE DAY ♪

13:34.985 --> 13:40.090
♪ I KNOW YOU'VE GOT YOUR PART ♪

13:40.090 --> 13:43.323
(Amanda laughing)

13:43.323 --> 13:46.296
♪ AND I'M WAITING FOR THE DAY ♪

13:46.296 --> 13:48.198
HEY, YOU WANT TO KNOW
A TRICK?
 YEAH.

13:48.198 --> 13:50.400
YOU PLANT YOUR FEET
IN THE SAND

13:50.400 --> 13:52.532
AND YOU STAND STILL
THROUGH THE WHOLE FIRST WAVE.
 OKAY.

13:52.532 --> 13:54.134
THEN THE NEXT WAVE'S
GONNA FEEL WARMER.
 OKAY.

13:54.134 --> 13:55.936
AND THEN THE ONE AFTER THAT'S
GONNA FEEL WARMER STILL.

13:55.936 --> 13:58.138
FINALLY, YOU'RE BARELY GONNA
NOTICE THE COLD AT ALL.

13:58.138 --> 13:59.569
(laughs)

13:59.569 --> 14:01.541
ARE YOU READY?
 YEAH.

14:01.541 --> 14:02.973
HERE IT COMES.

14:02.973 --> 14:04.344
OKAY. AAH!

14:04.344 --> 14:06.516
YOU MUST COME FROM
A FAMILY OF POLAR BEARS.

14:06.516 --> 14:09.019
THAT WATER IS ICE COLD.

14:09.019 --> 14:10.520
ONLY AT FIRST.

14:10.520 --> 14:13.323
AFTER A WHILE,
YOU CAN'T FEEL ANYTHING.

14:13.323 --> 14:14.624
SOUNDS LIKE MY MARRIAGE.

14:14.624 --> 14:15.886
(chuckles)

14:15.886 --> 14:17.427
YOU MUST BE THE NEW RENTER.

14:17.427 --> 14:19.189
EMILY THORNE.

14:19.189 --> 14:21.031
WORD GETS AROUND FAST.

14:21.031 --> 14:22.532
LIKE LIGHTNING.

14:22.532 --> 14:24.034
I'M LYDIA DAVIS.

14:24.034 --> 14:26.136
MY HUSBAND AND I OWN
THE HOUSE YOU'RE STAYING IN.

14:26.136 --> 14:27.597
OH. (laughs)

14:27.597 --> 14:29.499
OH, WOW.

14:29.499 --> 14:31.101
IT'S SO NICE TO MEET YOU.

14:31.101 --> 14:33.173
I CAN'T TELL YOU
HOW MUCH I LOVE IT.

14:33.173 --> 14:35.345
ME, TOO.

14:35.345 --> 14:37.877
SOME GOOD MEMORIES
WERE MADE THERE.

14:37.877 --> 14:41.451
WELL, HOPEFULLY I CAN MAKE
SOME OF MY OWN.

14:41.451 --> 14:44.514
SO LONG AS WE DON'T HAVE TO TAKE
IT OUT OF YOUR DAMAGE DEPOSIT.

14:44.514 --> 14:46.886
WELCOME TO THE HAMPTONS.

14:46.886 --> 14:52.122
♪ WHAT DO YOU TAKE ME FOR? ♪

14:52.122 --> 14:55.325
♪ HOLD ON ♪

14:55.325 --> 14:59.970
♪ WHAT DID YOU SAY THAT FOR? ♪

14:59.970 --> 15:01.471
(man) FEDERAL PROSECUTORS

15:01.471 --> 15:03.273
WRAPPED UP THEIR CASE
FOR TREASON

15:03.273 --> 15:06.236
AGAINST DISGRACED HEDGE FUND
EXECUTIVE DAVID CLARKE.

15:06.236 --> 15:07.978
TAKING THE STAND
WAS CLARKE'S SECRETARY,

15:07.978 --> 15:09.339
LYDIA DAVIS,

15:09.339 --> 15:11.581
WHOSE TESTIMONY SUPPORTED
THE DAMNING ALLEGATIONS

15:11.581 --> 15:13.944
MADE BY CLARKE'S FORMER BOSS,

15:13.944 --> 15:15.145
CONRAD GRAYSON.

15:15.145 --> 15:17.117
GRAYSON'S TESTIMONY
DETAILED THE SCHEME

15:17.117 --> 15:19.119
CLARKE USED TO CHANNEL MONEY
TO THE TERRORISTS

15:19.119 --> 15:22.692
RESPONSIBLE FOR THE DOWNING
OF FLIGHT 1-9-7.

15:22.692 --> 15:26.356
ALL 246 AMERICANS ONBOARD
THAT FLIGHT WERE KILLED.

15:26.356 --> 15:28.358
(Amanda) WHAT DO YOU
LIKE BETTER, DAD,

15:28.358 --> 15:30.660
SEA GLASS OR STARFISH?

15:30.660 --> 15:31.962
DAD?

15:31.962 --> 15:33.263
STARFISH, DEFINITELY.

15:33.263 --> 15:34.404
HERE YOU GO.
 (telephone ringing)

15:34.404 --> 15:35.405
THANK YOU.

15:35.405 --> 15:37.007
(dog barking)

15:37.007 --> 15:38.938
(beeps)
 David, it's Victoria.

15:38.938 --> 15:41.071
HEY, DO YOU MIND GOING
AND LOOKING AFTER SAMMY FOR ME?

15:41.071 --> 15:43.373
SURE.
 David, are you there?

15:43.373 --> 15:44.474
WHAT'S THE MATTER, SAMMY?

15:44.474 --> 15:46.476
HEY, EVERYTHING OKAY?
 WHATCHA DOIN'?

15:46.476 --> 15:48.248
(Sammy yelps, guns click)
 DADDY!

15:48.248 --> 15:50.720
WHOA, WHOA. WHAT'S GOING ON?
 (Amanda screaming)

15:50.720 --> 15:52.322
HANDS UP SO I CAN SEE 'EM.
 WHAT'S GOING ON?

15:52.322 --> 15:54.354
YOU'RE MAKING A MIS--WAIT!
YOU'RE MAKING A MISTAKE!

15:54.354 --> 15:55.986
GET YOUR HANDS OFF MY DAUGHTER!
 AAH! NO!

15:55.986 --> 15:57.657
GET YOUR HANDS
OFF MY DAUGHTER!
 (screaming)

15:57.657 --> 15:58.728
AMANDA! LET HER GO!

15:58.728 --> 15:59.990
(continues screaming)

15:59.990 --> 16:01.661
AMANDA! AMANDA!

16:01.661 --> 16:03.063
(Amanda) AAH!

16:03.063 --> 16:05.535
(Lydia) DAVID CLARKE
HAD EVERYONE FOOLED,

16:05.535 --> 16:06.966
INCLUDING ME.

16:06.966 --> 16:10.200
I'M JUST GLAD I CAN HELP PUT
THAT MONSTER AWAY.

16:12.142 --> 16:16.246
(clicking button)

16:21.681 --> 16:23.613
(beeps)

16:35.695 --> 16:38.668
NO ONE IS TO APPROACH
THE HEAD TABLE

16:38.668 --> 16:41.000
UNLESS THEY'RE ESCORTED BY
EITHER MYSELF OR MRS. GRAYSON.

16:41.000 --> 16:43.073
I CANNOT STRESS HOW IMPORTANT
THAT SEATING CHART IS.

16:43.073 --> 16:44.574
GOT IT?
 I GOT IT.

16:44.574 --> 16:45.735
GOOD.

16:45.735 --> 16:47.507
AT 2:00,
SECURITY WILL BE DELIVERING

16:47.507 --> 16:48.638
MRS. GRAYSON'S MANET

16:48.638 --> 16:50.510
TO BE SET UP FOR AUCTION
IN THE MAIN CABIN.

16:50.510 --> 16:51.641
OKAY?
 (cell phone rings)

16:51.641 --> 16:53.113
(sighs)
 JENKINS.

16:53.113 --> 16:54.444
(rings and beeps)
 (speaking indistinctly)

16:54.444 --> 16:56.216
EMS, PLEASE DON'T KILL ME.

16:56.216 --> 16:57.387
WELL, THAT DEPENDS.

16:57.387 --> 16:59.219
WHAT AM I
NOT KILLING YOU FOR?

16:59.219 --> 17:01.321
Standing you up
this afternoon.

17:01.321 --> 17:03.293
I have a million-dollar
art auction to deal with.

17:03.293 --> 17:05.295
(camera phone shutter clicks)

17:05.295 --> 17:06.455
OH,
THERE'S NO PRESSURE THERE.

17:06.455 --> 17:07.797
YOU WANT ME TO PICK UP
YOUR DRESS FOR YOU?

17:07.797 --> 17:10.230
OH, YOU'RE A LIFESAVER.

17:10.230 --> 17:11.560
OH, PLEASE. I'M SIGHTSEEING.
YOU'RE WORKING.

17:11.560 --> 17:12.702
I GOT YOU COVERED.

17:12.702 --> 17:14.064
Thank you.

17:14.064 --> 17:15.305
BYE.

17:15.305 --> 17:18.808
(indistinct conversations)

17:20.670 --> 17:23.643
(keypad beeping)

17:23.643 --> 17:26.646
(indistinct conversations
continue)

17:30.120 --> 17:32.252
MORE TEA?

17:35.085 --> 17:36.756
PLEASE.

17:38.628 --> 17:40.630
DO YOU THINK I'M TAN ENOUGH
FOR MY FIRST DAY ON THE BEACH

17:40.630 --> 17:42.732
OR DO I NEED ANOTHER SPRAY?

17:42.732 --> 17:44.834
WHAT YOU NEED
IS ANOTHER BATHING SUIT.

17:44.834 --> 17:46.466
COMPARED TO WHAT THE REST
OF MY FRIENDS ARE WEARING,

17:46.466 --> 17:48.198
THIS IS PRACTICALLY
A BURKA.

17:48.198 --> 17:49.839
(tires squeal)
 UNLIKE THE REST
OF YOUR FRIENDS...

17:49.839 --> 17:52.071
(engine revving)
 IT'S IMPORTANT TO ME
THAT YOU DON'T END UP

17:52.071 --> 17:54.374
ON "PAGE SIX" AT ONE OF
DIDDY'S HOT TUB PARTIES.

17:54.374 --> 17:56.246
DANNY'S HOME.

18:00.710 --> 18:02.582
(closes car door)

18:04.684 --> 18:06.716
OOH, DANNY! (laughs)

18:06.716 --> 18:08.258
AH. (laughs)

18:08.258 --> 18:10.190
(laughs)
 HOW YOU DOING?

18:10.190 --> 18:11.621
(laughs)
 OH.

18:11.621 --> 18:14.194
I'M SO HAPPY TO SEE YOU.

18:14.194 --> 18:16.826
I'M SO GLAD TO SEE YOU.
WHAT'S GOING ON, A FIRE SALE?

18:16.826 --> 18:19.369
(man speaking indistinctly)
 CHARITY STUNT.

18:19.369 --> 18:21.371
WELCOME HOME, DANIEL.

18:21.371 --> 18:22.832
HI, MOM.

18:22.832 --> 18:24.434
I'M HEADED DOWN
TO THE BEACH.

18:24.434 --> 18:25.435
OKAY.

18:25.435 --> 18:26.576
OKAY.

18:26.576 --> 18:27.777
(Daniel)
SHE'S GROWING UP FAST.

18:27.777 --> 18:30.580
(laughs) TOO FAST.

18:32.682 --> 18:33.813
YOU HUNGRY?

18:33.813 --> 18:35.315
YOU KNOW,
I'M A LITTLE WIPED OUT.

18:35.315 --> 18:36.446
I THINK I'LL JUST
LAY DOWN FOR A BIT.

18:36.446 --> 18:38.488
YEAH, YOU LOOK A LITTLE TIRED.

18:38.488 --> 18:40.220
WELL, STUDYING
WILL DO THAT TO A GUY.

18:40.220 --> 18:42.452
MM. SO WILL PARTYING.
 MOM, I JUST GOT HERE.

18:42.452 --> 18:43.793
GIVE ME A BREAK.
 (laughs)

18:43.793 --> 18:45.124
WHERE'S DAD, GOLFING?

18:45.124 --> 18:46.456
WHERE ELSE?

18:46.456 --> 18:48.798
YEP. WHERE ELSE?

18:48.798 --> 18:49.859
(sighs)

18:49.859 --> 18:51.831
(panting) NOW...

18:51.831 --> 18:53.533
IT FEELS LIKE SUMMER.

18:53.533 --> 18:56.536
(laughs)

18:56.536 --> 18:57.837
CHAMPAGNE?

18:57.837 --> 18:59.839
(exhales)
YOU HAVE TO ASK?

18:59.839 --> 19:01.371
OH.

19:01.371 --> 19:02.812
MM. (growls)

19:02.812 --> 19:03.773
(inhales sharply)

19:03.773 --> 19:06.145
(groans)

19:06.145 --> 19:07.647
(exhales deeply)

19:07.647 --> 19:08.848
(objects clatter)

19:08.848 --> 19:11.521
(Lydia exhales deeply)

19:11.521 --> 19:13.353
AH.

19:13.353 --> 19:14.924
(inhales sharply)

19:14.924 --> 19:16.826
AH... (grunts)

19:16.826 --> 19:18.858
(groans)
 CONRAD?

19:18.858 --> 19:20.660
WHAT'S WRONG?
 (grunts)

19:20.660 --> 19:22.332
(grunt)
 ARE YOU OKAY?

19:22.332 --> 19:23.833
(groans)
 CONRAD.

19:23.833 --> 19:25.535
(grunts)
 OH, GOD.

19:25.535 --> 19:27.537
♪♪♪

19:27.537 --> 19:30.169
ALL RIGHT, SO THE FIRST THING
YOU DO IS ENTER THE CODE.

19:30.169 --> 19:31.841
(keypad beeping)
 IT'S NOT EXACTLY...

19:31.841 --> 19:33.743
OOH.
 THEN YOU SWIPE THE CARD.

19:33.743 --> 19:34.944
THEN THE AMOUNT.

19:34.944 --> 19:35.905
ARE WE EATING IN HERE?

19:35.905 --> 19:38.208
UH, YEAH.
I'M AFRAID SO.

19:38.208 --> 19:39.609
DEC.

19:39.609 --> 19:41.611
YEAH, YEAH, I GOT IT. UH,
CARD, SWIPE, AMOUNT, RIGHT?

19:41.611 --> 19:43.283
CODE, SWIPE, AMOUNT.

19:43.283 --> 19:45.855
JACK, WILL YOU TAKE CARE
OF THE MEAN GIRLS' TABLE?

19:45.855 --> 19:48.758
IT'S TOO EARLY IN THE SEASON
FOR ME TO START MAKING ENEMIES.

19:48.758 --> 19:50.290
WHY SHOULD THIS YEAR
BE ANY DIFFERENT?

19:50.290 --> 19:52.222
BECAUSE YOU'RE SAILING OFF
TO SAVE THE WORLD,

19:52.222 --> 19:54.224
AND THIS PLACE CAN'T AFFORD
BAD PRESS.

19:54.224 --> 19:55.525
YEAH, YEAH, I, UH,

19:55.525 --> 19:56.896
I GOT IT. OKAY?

19:56.896 --> 19:58.898
(indistinct conversations)

19:58.898 --> 20:01.801
(panting)

20:01.801 --> 20:04.634
HI. HELP YOU?

20:04.634 --> 20:05.935
UM, ARE YOU THE OWNER?

20:05.935 --> 20:08.278
HOPEFULLY NOT FOR ANOTHER
30 YEARS OR SO.

20:08.278 --> 20:10.440
YOU'RE LOOKING FOR MY DAD.

20:10.440 --> 20:12.382
SOME SUIT'S
LOOKING FOR YOU.

20:12.382 --> 20:13.483
YOU ARE?

20:13.483 --> 20:14.984
UM, DOUG REID
WITH FIRST FEDERAL.

20:14.984 --> 20:17.587
OH, MR. REID.
I'LL TAKE CARE OF HIM, JACK.

20:17.587 --> 20:18.888
HEY, MR. REID.
CARL PORTER.

20:18.888 --> 20:19.889
NICE TO MEET YOU.

20:19.889 --> 20:21.321
THANKS FOR COMING DOWN.

20:21.321 --> 20:24.254
WHY DON'T YOU FOLLOW ME
TO MY OFFICE?

20:24.254 --> 20:25.755
(girl) I KNOW YOU LIKE HIM.
HERE HE COMES.

20:25.755 --> 20:26.926
LADIES.

20:26.926 --> 20:28.458
WE'LL TAKE
THREE RUM AND DIETS.

20:28.458 --> 20:31.301
UH, GONNA NEED TO SEE I.D.s.

20:31.301 --> 20:33.603
UM, WE LEFT OUR I.D.s
AT THE BEACH,

20:33.603 --> 20:34.804
BUT WE HAVE PLENTY OF MONEY.

20:34.804 --> 20:35.935
(chuckles)

20:35.935 --> 20:37.367
YEAH.

20:37.367 --> 20:39.609
SORRY. I'M NOT INTERESTED
IN YOUR MONEY.

20:39.609 --> 20:43.643
(indistinct conversations)

20:43.643 --> 20:45.945
ARE YOU INTERESTED
IN MY PHONE NUMBER?

20:45.945 --> 20:47.947
(indistinct conversations
continue)

20:47.947 --> 20:49.248
(siren wails)
 IT LOOKS LIKE A STEMI.

20:49.248 --> 20:50.750
WE NEED TO GET HIM IN QUICK.

20:50.750 --> 20:51.981
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

20:51.981 --> 20:53.583
IS HE GONNA BE OKAY?

20:53.583 --> 20:55.254
MA'AM, I NEED YOU
TO STEP BACK, PLEASE.

20:55.254 --> 20:56.386
WHERE ARE YOU TAKING HIM?

20:56.386 --> 20:57.687
SOUTHFORK HOSPITAL.

20:57.687 --> 20:59.359
LYDIA. LYDIA.
 NICE AND EASY,
ON MY COUNT.

20:59.359 --> 21:00.890
ONE, TWO...
 EMILY THORNE.

21:00.890 --> 21:03.733
THREE.
 MY--MY GOD.
IS THIS YOUR HUSBAND?

21:03.733 --> 21:06.596
DO YOU NEED A RIDE
TO THE HOSPITAL?
 (paramedics
speaking indistinctly)

21:06.596 --> 21:08.838
NO, I DON'T. I--

21:08.838 --> 21:10.740
(monitor beeping erratically)

21:10.740 --> 21:13.743
(emergency radio chatter)

21:13.743 --> 21:15.405
(paramedics continue
speaking indistinctly)

21:15.405 --> 21:17.447
(emergency radio chatter
continues)

21:17.447 --> 21:19.679
(groans)

21:19.679 --> 21:21.851
(man) ...AND AN E.K.G.
AS SOON AS WE GET THERE.

21:21.851 --> 21:24.854
(indistinct conversations)

21:24.854 --> 21:26.356
♪♪♪

21:26.356 --> 21:27.917
(Jack) SAMMY.

21:27.917 --> 21:29.419
♪♪♪

21:29.419 --> 21:31.461
THE WHOLE POINT OF FETCH
IS TO BRING THE STICK BACK

21:31.461 --> 21:32.622
WHEN I THROW IT.

21:32.622 --> 21:34.023
I REALLY GOTTA
EXPLAIN THIS AGAIN?

21:34.023 --> 21:35.024
(barks)

21:35.024 --> 21:36.295
COME HERE.

21:36.295 --> 21:37.797
(barking)
 (Amanda laughs)
COME HERE, SAMMY.

21:37.797 --> 21:39.028
I FOUND A STICK FOR YOU.

21:39.028 --> 21:40.830
WHAT'S HIS NAME?
 SAM.

21:40.830 --> 21:42.031
(both laugh)

21:42.031 --> 21:43.403
HE SURE LIKES STICKS.

21:44.804 --> 21:46.806
FETCH IT, SAMMY.

21:46.806 --> 21:47.937
NICE THROW.

21:47.937 --> 21:49.479
THANKS.

21:49.479 --> 21:50.880
I'M JACK.

21:50.880 --> 21:52.041
I'M AMANDA.

21:52.041 --> 21:54.043
(Jack) COME ON, SAMMY.
PICK UP THE STICK.

21:54.043 --> 21:55.385
(whines)

21:55.385 --> 21:57.617
WHERE YOU GOING?

21:57.617 --> 21:59.088
GET BACK HERE.
 (panting)

21:59.088 --> 22:01.020
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
 (whines)

22:01.020 --> 22:03.052
SAMMY.
 (whines)

22:03.052 --> 22:04.794
SAM?

22:04.794 --> 22:06.656
(pants) BARKS.
 SAMMY!

22:06.656 --> 22:08.958
(laughing)
 SAMMY! GET DOWN.

22:08.958 --> 22:11.701
WHAT'S THE MATTER WITH YOU?
I'M SORRY.

22:11.701 --> 22:12.902
HE'S NOT NORMALLY
THIS FRIENDLY.

22:12.902 --> 22:15.004
HE'S KIND OF AN OLD GRUMP,
ACTUALLY.

22:15.004 --> 22:16.866
(Sammy panting)
 MM.

22:16.866 --> 22:18.838
OH, HE GOT MUD
ON YOUR DRESS.

22:18.838 --> 22:20.339
OH, THAT'S NO BIG DEAL.

22:20.339 --> 22:21.841
THERE'S AN EARL AND EMMA'S
DRY CLEANERS

22:21.841 --> 22:22.972
RIGHT AROUND THE CORNER.

22:22.972 --> 22:24.974
I'LL WALK YOU OVER.

22:24.974 --> 22:26.976
OH, THAT'S OKAY.
UM, I GOT IT.

22:26.976 --> 22:28.718
THANKS.
 WELL, HEY.

22:28.718 --> 22:30.019
UH, TELL EARL AND EMMA

22:30.019 --> 22:32.351
THAT YOU'RE A FRIEND
OF JACK PORTER'S.

22:32.351 --> 22:34.854
MY FAMILY OWNS THE TAVERN DOWN
BY THE DOCKS, THE STOWAWAY.

22:34.854 --> 22:36.355
WHAT'S--WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

22:36.355 --> 22:38.388
I'LL... PUT YOU ON
THE OFFICIAL COMP LIST.

22:38.388 --> 22:39.989
YOU DON'T HAVE TO DO THAT.

22:39.989 --> 22:42.692
WELL, I'M NOT PICKING UP
THE TAB. SAMMY IS.

22:42.692 --> 22:45.535
HE FEELS TERRIBLE.
DON'T YOU?

22:45.535 --> 22:46.696
(Sammy whimpers)

22:46.696 --> 22:47.937
THANKS ANYWAY.

22:47.937 --> 22:49.569
ALL RIGHTY, THEN.

22:49.569 --> 22:52.071
(people speaking indistinctly)

22:52.071 --> 22:54.003
YOU HAVE A GREAT SUMMER.

22:54.003 --> 22:55.805
(barks)

22:55.805 --> 22:58.077
(engine turns over)

22:58.077 --> 23:00.980
(car drives away)

23:00.980 --> 23:03.983
(woman speaking indistinctly
over p.a.)

23:05.415 --> 23:09.088
(panting)

23:09.088 --> 23:12.161
(curtain rings clatter)

23:12.161 --> 23:14.624
HEY.
 OH, MY GOD, CONRAD.

23:14.624 --> 23:16.796
I THOUGHT I WAS GOING TO
FIND YOU DEAD.
 I'M FINE.

23:16.796 --> 23:18.127
WHAT HAPPENED?

23:18.127 --> 23:19.999
ACUTE ABDOMINAL DYSPEPSIA.

23:19.999 --> 23:22.031
THE REMORSE
OF A GUILTY STOMACH.

23:22.031 --> 23:24.974
YOUR STAFF MADE IT SOUND AS IF
HE WAS HAVING A HEART ATTACK.

23:24.974 --> 23:26.436
WELL,
DEPENDING ON THE SEVERITY,

23:26.436 --> 23:27.937
THE SYMPTOMS
CAN BE IDENTICAL.

23:27.937 --> 23:29.509
AS FAR AS I CAN TELL,
YOUR HUSBAND'S

23:29.509 --> 23:31.010
AS HEALTHY
AS A THOROUGHBRED.

23:31.010 --> 23:32.782
BUT I DO SUGGEST
THAT HE STAY AWAY

23:32.782 --> 23:34.814
FROM THE SOUTHFORK INN'S
SPICY BISQUE FOR A WHILE.

23:34.814 --> 23:35.815
(exhales)

23:35.815 --> 23:38.047
THE SOUTHFORK INN?

23:38.047 --> 23:39.048
YEAH.

23:39.048 --> 23:41.150
I THOUGHT YOU WENT GOLFING.

23:41.150 --> 23:43.523
YEAH, I DID, EARLIER.

23:43.523 --> 23:46.826
SOUTHFORK IS A HALF-HOUR
IN THE OPPOSITE DIRECTION.

23:46.826 --> 23:49.559
I'M AWARE OF THAT.

23:49.559 --> 23:50.930
EXCUSE ME.

23:50.930 --> 23:52.862
COME ON. YOU KNOW
I JUST GET IN THE WAY

23:52.862 --> 23:54.103
WHEN YOU'RE PLANNING
ONE OF YOUR PARTIES.

23:54.103 --> 23:56.035
I JUST THOUGHT
I WOULD GO FOR A DRIVE

23:56.035 --> 23:57.967
AND STAY OUT OF YOUR HAIR
FOR A WHILE.
 (chuckles)

23:57.967 --> 23:59.569
AND I'M SORRY
THAT I SCARED YOU.

23:59.569 --> 24:01.440
(elevator bell dings)

24:01.440 --> 24:04.874
(indistinct conversations)

24:10.480 --> 24:12.622
DON'T DO IT AGAIN.

24:22.191 --> 24:24.964
(people speaking indistinctly)

24:24.964 --> 24:26.896
♪♪♪

24:26.896 --> 24:28.167
(Ashley) EMILY.

24:28.167 --> 24:29.168
HEY.

24:29.168 --> 24:30.500
YOU LOOK AMAZING.

24:30.500 --> 24:32.201
I LOOK AMAZING? LOOK AT YOU.
LOOK AT THIS PARTY.

24:32.201 --> 24:33.973
CONGRATULATIONS.

24:33.973 --> 24:36.475
WELL, IT'S TOO EARLY FOR THAT.
HAVEN'T YOU SEEN "TITANIC"?

24:36.475 --> 24:37.547
(laughs)

24:37.547 --> 24:38.908
SO HOW WELL
DO YOU KNOW THESE PEOPLE?

24:38.908 --> 24:40.479
WELL ENOUGH TO KNOW
WHO TO KEEP AWAY FROM

24:40.479 --> 24:41.811
AND WHO TO SNUGGLE UP TO.

24:41.811 --> 24:43.212
MM. QUICK TUTORIAL?
 OKAY.

24:43.212 --> 24:44.884
THE GIRL IN THE ORANGE
ESCADA DRESS?

24:44.884 --> 24:45.955
MM-HMM.

24:45.955 --> 24:47.216
THAT'S
MAYOR BLOOMBERG'S NIECE.

24:47.216 --> 24:48.487
AND THE WOMAN
SHE'S TALKING TO,

24:48.487 --> 24:50.560
NOW THIS ONE IS IMPORTANT--

24:50.560 --> 24:51.891
MEGAN FOSTER.

24:51.891 --> 24:53.192
(whispers) SHOE BUYER
FOR BARNEYS OF NEW YORK.

24:53.192 --> 24:54.193
OOH.

24:54.193 --> 24:57.196
♪♪♪

24:57.196 --> 24:58.928
(indistinct conversations)

24:58.928 --> 25:01.230
GRAY SUIT BOY
IS KINDA CUTE.

25:01.230 --> 25:02.932
(Ashley)
THAT'S DANIEL GRAYSON,

25:02.932 --> 25:05.134
VICTORIA'S
TRAGICALLY PRIVILEGED SPAWN.

25:05.134 --> 25:08.507
DANIEL WRAPPED HIS CONVERTIBLE
AROUND A TREE LAST SUMMER

25:08.507 --> 25:09.779
AFTER ONE TOO MANY.

25:09.779 --> 25:11.811
DIDN'T HURT HIS FACE MUCH.

25:11.811 --> 25:13.512
YEAH, IT DIDN'T WORK OUT
QUITE AS WELL

25:13.512 --> 25:15.014
FOR THE WAITRESS
HE WAS SHAGGING.

25:15.014 --> 25:16.986
HIS PARENTS PAID OFF
EVERYONE AND THEIR MOTHER

25:16.986 --> 25:19.518
TO KEEP HIM OUT OF JAIL.

25:19.518 --> 25:21.821
AND THE PLOT THICKENS.

25:21.821 --> 25:23.522
WHO'S THAT?
 (Nolan) YOU EVER BEEN
ON A PRIVATE JET?

25:23.522 --> 25:25.024
NOLAN ROSS.
 I'VE GOT TWO.

25:25.024 --> 25:26.525
FORMER TECH BOOM WHIZ KID

25:26.525 --> 25:28.027
AND PERENNIAL
PAIN IN THE ASS.

25:28.027 --> 25:30.630
IF YOU EMPTIED THE BANK ACCOUNTS
OF EVERYONE AT THIS PARTY,

25:30.630 --> 25:32.802
IT WOULDN'T ADD UP
TO THE INTEREST...
 THERE HE IS...

25:32.802 --> 25:34.303
HIS MAKES IN A WEEK.
 OLD BLUE EYES.

25:34.303 --> 25:36.005
(Conrad) NOLAN...
 (lowered voice) AND THAT

25:36.005 --> 25:37.106
IS QUEEN VICTORIA.

25:37.106 --> 25:38.768
WOW.
 HELLO, NOLAN.

25:38.768 --> 25:39.839
HELLO, VICTORIA.

25:39.839 --> 25:41.270
HOW ARE YOU?

25:41.270 --> 25:44.273
(guests speaking indistinctly)

25:49.278 --> 25:52.321
(speaks inaudibly)

26:07.797 --> 26:11.570
I THINK SHE SPOTTED YOU.

26:12.772 --> 26:15.344
GOOD.

26:15.344 --> 26:17.346
INTRODUCE US.

26:17.346 --> 26:20.650
♪♪♪

26:20.650 --> 26:22.251
HEY, HOW ABOUT
THAT STOCK SPLIT, HUH?

26:22.251 --> 26:23.713
WHAT'D I TELL YOU?
 TURNED OUT GREAT.

26:23.713 --> 26:25.214
CONRAD.
 YEAH.

26:25.214 --> 26:26.886
WE WEREN'T SURE WE WERE GOING
TO SEE YOU THIS AFTERNOON.

26:26.886 --> 26:28.587
HUH?
 RUMOR HAD IT THAT YOU, UH,

26:28.587 --> 26:30.219
REALLY DODGED A BULLET
YESTERDAY.

26:30.219 --> 26:32.722
OH, WELL, I'M HAPPY TO REPORT
THAT THE RUMORS OF MY DEMISE

26:32.722 --> 26:34.263
ARE GREATLY EXAGGERATED.

26:34.263 --> 26:35.995
OH. WELL, I'M THRILLED
TO HEAR IT.

26:35.995 --> 26:37.296
I'LL BE SURE
TO SPREAD THE WORD.

26:37.296 --> 26:39.028
OH, I'M SURE YOU WILL.

26:39.028 --> 26:40.169
LYDIA.

26:40.169 --> 26:43.232
♪♪♪

26:43.232 --> 26:45.604
I JUST...
(speaks indistinctly)

26:45.604 --> 26:47.837
(indistinct conversations)

26:47.837 --> 26:49.278
KARRIE, YOU LOOK LIKE
YOU COULD USE ANOTHER DRINK.

26:49.278 --> 26:51.280
DARLING, WOULD YOU PLEASE
SHOW HER THE WAY TO THE BAR?

26:51.280 --> 26:52.842
SURE.

26:52.842 --> 26:54.243
LYDIA.

26:54.243 --> 26:57.146
WHERE HAVE YOU
BEEN HIDING YOURSELF?

26:57.146 --> 26:59.148
I LEFT THREE MESSAGES
FOR YOU.

26:59.148 --> 27:02.021
(Ashley) MRS. GRAYSON,
FORGIVE ME FOR INTERRUPTING.

27:02.021 --> 27:04.694
I JUST WANTED TO INTRODUCE YOU
TO A DEAR FRIEND OF MINE.

27:04.694 --> 27:06.856
VICTORIA GRAYSON,
EMILY THORNE.

27:06.856 --> 27:09.058
HELLO, MRS. GRAYSON.
 AH, MS. THORNE.

27:09.058 --> 27:10.359
I WAS WONDERING
WHO THE LATE ENTRY WAS

27:10.359 --> 27:11.901
ON THE GUEST ROSTER.

27:11.901 --> 27:13.362
WELL, EMILY'S NEW
TO THE HAMPTONS,

27:13.362 --> 27:15.665
BUT SHE REALLY WANTED TO
TAKE PART IN YOUR FUND-RAISER.

27:15.665 --> 27:17.166
OH. HOW DO YOU TWO
KNOW EACH OTHER?

27:17.166 --> 27:19.168
WE VOLUNTEERED TOGETHER
AT THE MET THIS WINTER.

27:19.168 --> 27:20.940
MM.
 APPARENTLY BEING
A SUSTAINING PATRON

27:20.940 --> 27:23.342
JUST WASN'T ENOUGH
FOR EMILY.

27:23.342 --> 27:26.716
MM. I TRY TO GIVE BACK
AS MUCH AS I CAN.

27:26.716 --> 27:28.948
LYDIA. HI.

27:28.948 --> 27:30.720
OH, DON'T TELL ME

27:30.720 --> 27:32.952
YOU'VE TAKEN UP VOLUNTEERING
AT THE MET AS WELL.

27:32.952 --> 27:34.754
(laughs)

27:34.754 --> 27:37.086
EMILY'S RENTING MY HOUSE
FOR THE SUMMER.

27:37.086 --> 27:38.387
AH.

27:38.387 --> 27:40.359
WE MET BRIEFLY ON THE BEACH.

27:40.359 --> 27:42.091
AND THEN YESTERDAY
AT THE SOUTHFORK INN.

27:42.091 --> 27:43.963
I HOPE YOUR HUSBAND'S
FEELING BETTER.

27:43.963 --> 27:46.365
♪♪♪

27:46.365 --> 27:49.739
(indistinct conversations)

28:01.380 --> 28:03.182
MM.

28:03.182 --> 28:05.815
(indistinct conversations
continue)

28:05.815 --> 28:08.057
♪♪♪

28:08.057 --> 28:10.459
VICTORIA, WAIT.

28:10.459 --> 28:13.462
(indistinct conversations
continue)

28:17.696 --> 28:19.468
(Carl)
EVERYONE, LISTEN UP, PLEASE.

28:19.468 --> 28:21.470
I JUST WANT TO THANK YOU ALL
FOR HELPING THE STOWAWAY

28:21.470 --> 28:23.903
KICK OFF THE SEASON RIGHT.
 (man) YOU'RE WELCOME!

28:23.903 --> 28:25.074
(man shouts indistinctly)

28:25.074 --> 28:28.908
(cheering)

28:28.908 --> 28:31.180
WHERE WERE YOU PEOPLE
ALL WINTER?

28:31.180 --> 28:34.744
(all laugh)

28:34.744 --> 28:37.446
TOMORROW MY SON JACK
IS SETTING SAIL FOR HAITI

28:37.446 --> 28:39.448
TO PITCH IN WITH THE RED CROSS.
 (men) GOOD LUCK, JACK!

28:39.448 --> 28:41.220
HE WANTED TO GO
RIGHT AFTER THE QUAKE,

28:41.220 --> 28:43.052
BUT I CONVINCED HIM TO
STICK AROUND AN EXTRA YEAR

28:43.052 --> 28:44.924
TO HELP ME OUT.

28:44.924 --> 28:47.256
ALMOST TWO, ACTUALLY,
BUT WHO'S COUNTING?

28:47.256 --> 28:48.828
WAS IT TWO?
 (laughs) YEAH.

28:48.828 --> 28:50.129
IT WAS TWO.

28:50.129 --> 28:51.400
(door closes,
bell on door jingles)

28:51.400 --> 28:52.802
(man)
GOOD GOING, JACK.

28:52.802 --> 28:54.804
(indistinct conversations)

28:54.804 --> 28:56.005
TO JACK!

28:56.005 --> 28:57.506
(all) TO JACK!

28:57.506 --> 28:59.909
I'M GONNA MISS YOU, SON.

28:59.909 --> 29:01.310
I'M GONNA MISS YOU, TOO.

29:01.310 --> 29:02.471
(man) YEAH, BABY!

29:02.471 --> 29:04.413
(Doug) MR. PORTER,
DO YOU HAVE A MOMENT?

29:04.413 --> 29:06.515
SURE.
RIGHT THIS WAY.

29:06.515 --> 29:08.978
(indistinct conversations
continue)

29:08.978 --> 29:11.951
THE BANK IS NOT GOING TO
APPROVE ANY FURTHER EXTENSIONS.

29:11.951 --> 29:14.123
BUT BUSINESS IS BACK.
ALL'S I NEED IS 30 MORE DAYS.

29:14.123 --> 29:15.484
I AM SORRY.
IT'S OUT OF MY HANDS.

29:15.484 --> 29:18.487
(indistinct conversations)

29:18.487 --> 29:21.791
(playing up-tempo
instrumental music)

29:21.791 --> 29:23.462
HERE WE GO ROUND AGAIN,
DANNY BOY,

29:23.462 --> 29:25.234
SUMMERTIME IN THE HAMPTONS.

29:25.234 --> 29:26.765
YEP.

29:26.765 --> 29:30.199
SAME PEOPLE,
SAME PARTIES...

29:30.199 --> 29:31.801
(music continues)

29:31.801 --> 29:33.772
SAME EVERYTHING.

29:33.772 --> 29:35.174
(indistinct conversations
continue)

29:35.174 --> 29:37.276
WHERE DO YOU WANT
TO DISCUSS IT?

29:37.276 --> 29:39.208
YO, MAN.

29:39.208 --> 29:41.480
WANT TO BUMP IT UP
A NOTCH?

29:41.480 --> 29:42.952
(music continues)

29:42.952 --> 29:45.014
OH, MY GOD!
 WOW.

29:45.014 --> 29:48.017
I'M SO SORRY.
GOD, I'M SUCH AN IDIOT.

29:48.017 --> 29:49.358
NO, DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

29:49.358 --> 29:50.489
IT'S, UH,
PROBABLY THE UNIVERSE

29:50.489 --> 29:52.862
TELLING ME
I NEED A COSTUME CHANGE.

29:52.862 --> 29:53.993
(chuckles)

29:53.993 --> 29:56.565
UH... I'M DANIEL.

29:56.565 --> 29:58.127
EMILY.

29:58.127 --> 29:59.869
HOW ABOUT I GET YOU
A DRY MARTINI?

29:59.869 --> 30:02.371
TWICE THE ALCOHOL,
HALF THE STAIN POTENTIAL.

30:02.371 --> 30:05.034
SURE. I'M SORRY.

30:05.034 --> 30:08.007
NO, NO. IT'S OKAY.
NOW WAIT RIGHT HERE.

30:08.007 --> 30:09.538
(music and indistinct
conversations continue)

30:09.538 --> 30:11.540
♪♪♪

30:11.540 --> 30:13.512
(indistinct conversations)

30:13.512 --> 30:15.484
HOW MUCH DOES HE OWE?

30:15.484 --> 30:17.546
I'M SORRY. THAT'S BETWEEN
YOUR DAD AND THE BANK.

30:17.546 --> 30:20.920
COME ON. HE'S OWNED
THE PLACE 30 YEARS.

30:20.920 --> 30:22.591
HOW BAD IS IT?

30:22.591 --> 30:25.194
THE BANK'S GONNA FORECLOSE
AT THE END OF THE MONTH.

30:25.194 --> 30:27.826
THE ONLY WAY TO STOP IT NOW
IS FULL PAYMENT ON ARREARS.

30:27.826 --> 30:29.899
I AM SORRY.
THERE'S NOTHING I CAN DO.

30:29.899 --> 30:32.902
♪♪♪

30:32.902 --> 30:36.405
(indistinct conversations
continue)

30:36.405 --> 30:39.909
♪♪♪

30:41.871 --> 30:43.873
(Victoria, amplified voice)
GOOD AFTERNOON, EVERYONE,

30:43.873 --> 30:45.214
AND HAPPY MEMORIAL DAY.

30:45.214 --> 30:46.916
(laughs)

30:46.916 --> 30:49.448
(people shouting indistinctly)

30:51.120 --> 30:53.052
(applause)

30:57.026 --> 30:59.989
I WANTED THE THEME
OF TODAY'S PARTY

30:59.989 --> 31:02.892
TO SIGNIFY A FRESH START
FOR ALL OF US.

31:02.892 --> 31:05.634
AS DIFFICULT AS
THE LAST FEW YEARS HAVE BEEN,

31:05.634 --> 31:08.167
THEY HAVE BEEN DEVASTATING
ON OUR CHARITIES.

31:08.167 --> 31:10.569
BUT NOW, AS THINGS ARE
BEGINNING TO TURN AROUND,

31:10.569 --> 31:12.271
I'M LOOKING FORWARD
TO GIVING BACK,

31:12.271 --> 31:13.602
AND I KNOW
THAT ALL OF YOU ARE, TOO.

31:13.602 --> 31:16.976
(guests laughing
and shouting indistinctly)

31:16.976 --> 31:19.478
SO TO START THINGS OFF RIGHT,

31:19.478 --> 31:22.351
I'D LIKE TO ANNOUNCE THE WINNER
OF THE ART AUCTION,

31:22.351 --> 31:26.615
MY DEAR FRIEND...

31:26.615 --> 31:28.357
LYDIA DAVIS...

31:28.357 --> 31:29.518
(woman) OH!

31:29.518 --> 31:31.290
(woman) CONGRATULATIONS.

31:31.290 --> 31:34.293
WHO WON'T BE GOING HOME
WITH THE MANET THIS EVENING,

31:34.293 --> 31:38.127
BUT WITH THE TREASURED van GOGH
THAT HANGS IN MY LIVING ROOM.

31:38.127 --> 31:42.201
(guests gasping
and speaking indistinctly)

31:42.201 --> 31:44.934
BUT I THOUGHT THE van GOGH WAS
A GIFT FROM LYDIA AND MICHAEL.

31:44.934 --> 31:48.277
(lowered voice) HAVE MS. DAVIS
ESCORTED OFF THE BOAT.

31:48.277 --> 31:50.209
(amplified voice)
AND IN RELATED NEWS,

31:50.209 --> 31:51.910
LYDIA HAS ASKED ME

31:51.910 --> 31:55.084
TO ANNOUNCE THAT THE BEACH HOUSE
SHE SHARED WITH HER HUSBAND

31:55.084 --> 31:57.386
IS OFFICIALLY ON THE MARKET.
 MS. DAVIS...

31:57.386 --> 31:59.618
(guard speaking indistinctly)
 I'M AFRAID THIS WILL BE

31:59.618 --> 32:01.120
HER FINAL WEEKEND
IN THE HAMPTONS.

32:01.120 --> 32:02.391
(guests speaking indistinctly)

32:02.391 --> 32:04.393
SO CALL YOUR REALTORS,
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,

32:04.393 --> 32:06.625
BECAUSE THIS ONE'S
GOING TO GO FAST.

32:06.625 --> 32:08.597
AND, LYDIA...

32:08.597 --> 32:10.099
WHEREVER YOU END UP,

32:10.099 --> 32:13.102
I HOPE THAT THE van GOGH
IS A CONSTANT REMINDER

32:13.102 --> 32:15.965
OF THE FRIENDSHIP WE SHARED.

32:15.965 --> 32:18.007
(guests continue
speaking indistinctly)

32:18.007 --> 32:21.510
(applause)

32:29.248 --> 32:31.450
(screaming)
 (David) GET YOUR HANDS
OFF MY DAUGHTER!

32:31.450 --> 32:32.721
(screams indistinctly)
 (man) I WANT THAT KID
OUTTA HERE. NOW!

32:32.721 --> 32:33.952
GIVE HER TO SOCIAL SERVICES!
 DADDY! (screaming)

32:33.952 --> 32:35.284
(David) AMANDA!
 (man) SETTLE DOWN!

32:35.284 --> 32:37.026
WHERE ARE YOU TAKING HER?!

32:37.026 --> 32:39.158
NO! DADDY!
 AMANDA! NO!

32:39.158 --> 32:41.690
SHE'S REALLY SOMETHING,
ISN'T SHE?

32:41.690 --> 32:43.962
MY MOTHER.

32:43.962 --> 32:45.634
SHE SURE IS.

32:45.634 --> 32:47.596
(man, amplified voice)
A BIG THANK-YOU ALSO...
 TO CHANCE MEETINGS.

32:47.596 --> 32:49.738
TO AN UNFORGETTABLE SUMMER.

32:49.738 --> 32:52.041
(man speaks indistinctly)

33:01.580 --> 33:03.012
HOW MANY HARVARD MEN
DOES IT TAKE

33:03.012 --> 33:04.313
TO SCREW IN A LIGHTBULB?
 I DON'T KNOW. HOW MANY?

33:04.313 --> 33:05.614
ONE, AND THE WHOLE WORLD
JUST REVOLVES AROUND HIM.

33:05.614 --> 33:06.655
(laughs)

33:06.655 --> 33:09.118
(laughs) ONE MORE?

33:09.118 --> 33:10.459
DRINK OR JOKE?

33:10.459 --> 33:12.121
EITHER. BOTH.

33:12.121 --> 33:13.622
MM. NEITHER.

33:13.622 --> 33:16.695
I AM JUST BUZZED ENOUGH
TO FIND THAT LAST JOKE FUNNY.

33:16.695 --> 33:19.498
ONE MORE, AND I MIGHT THINK
THAT YOU MEANT IT.

33:19.498 --> 33:21.670
BUT DON'T LET ME STOP YOU.

33:21.670 --> 33:24.673
OH, NO, NO. I'VE HAD ABOUT
ALL THE CLUB SODA I CAN TAKE.

33:24.673 --> 33:26.375
YOU DON'T DRINK?

33:26.375 --> 33:28.507
USED TO...

33:28.507 --> 33:29.678
EPICALLY.

33:29.678 --> 33:30.739
HMM.

33:30.739 --> 33:33.242
I GOTTA ADMIT, IT'S--

33:33.242 --> 33:36.545
IT'S NICE MEETING SOMEONE
WHO NEVER KNEW THE OLD ME.

33:36.545 --> 33:38.547
YEAH.

33:38.547 --> 33:40.689
I KNOW THE FEELING.

33:40.689 --> 33:44.723
♪♪♪

33:44.723 --> 33:46.525
DOUBLE INFINITY.

33:46.525 --> 33:48.357
♪♪♪

33:48.357 --> 33:50.259
SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

33:50.259 --> 33:51.760
THAT'S A LONG TIME.

33:51.760 --> 33:54.363
DANIEL...

33:54.363 --> 33:56.365
YOUR FATHER AND I
ARE LEAVING.

33:56.365 --> 33:59.037
THANK YOU FOR A LOVELY PARTY,
MRS. GRAYSON.

33:59.037 --> 34:00.709
IT WAS GREAT
MEETING BOTH OF YOU.

34:00.709 --> 34:02.711
WELL, NOW THAT YOU'VE
MOVED IN NEXT DOOR,

34:02.711 --> 34:05.714
I SUPPOSE WE'LL BE SEEING
A LOT OF YOU THIS SUMMER.

34:05.714 --> 34:07.746
♪♪♪

34:07.746 --> 34:09.777
I'LL EXPECT YOU SHORTLY,
DANIEL.

34:09.777 --> 34:12.751
♪♪♪

34:12.751 --> 34:14.723
(indistinct conversations
and laughter)

34:14.723 --> 34:16.554
DON'T LET MY MOM
RATTLE YOU.

34:16.554 --> 34:19.828
INTIMIDATION IS PRACTICALLY
A SIGN OF ENDEARMENT WITH HER.

34:19.828 --> 34:22.231
I'D HATE TO BE
ON HER BAD SIDE.

34:22.231 --> 34:24.233
YES, YOU WOULD.

34:24.233 --> 34:25.734
(both laugh)

34:25.734 --> 34:27.235
I SHOULD GO.

34:27.235 --> 34:29.697
UH, I'M HEADED YOUR WAY.
YOU NEED A RIDE?

34:29.697 --> 34:31.239
NO, THANKS.

34:31.239 --> 34:33.402
MAYBE NEXT TIME.

34:33.402 --> 34:35.774
TILL NEXT TIME.

34:35.774 --> 34:39.507
(indistinct conversations)

34:39.507 --> 34:41.780
♪♪♪

34:41.780 --> 34:44.813
(Conrad) YOU DIDN'T
HAVE TO EXILE HER.

34:44.813 --> 34:46.315
WHAT YOU DID WAS CRUEL.

34:46.315 --> 34:48.317
OH, WHAT I DID WAS CRUEL?
(laughs)

34:48.317 --> 34:49.818
YOU COULD HAVE HAD ANYONE,

34:49.818 --> 34:51.690
AND YOU KNEW SHE WAS
MY CLOSEST FRIEND.

34:51.690 --> 34:53.661
IT WAS NEVER MEANT
TO BE AN AFFAIR.

34:53.661 --> 34:55.664
OH, IT JUST HAPPENED?

34:55.664 --> 34:57.666
ARE YOU PHYSICALLY INCAPABLE
OF TAKING RESPONSIBILITY

34:57.666 --> 34:58.697
FOR YOUR ACTIONS?

34:58.697 --> 35:00.699
THERE IS A PROBLEM
WE SEEM TO SHARE.

35:00.699 --> 35:02.701
IF YOU'LL REMEMBER,
I GAVE UP EVERYTHING ONCE

35:02.701 --> 35:04.503
TO PROVE HOW MUCH I LOVE YOU.

35:04.503 --> 35:07.206
I RETURNED THE FAVOR.
I HELPED YOU DESTROY A MAN.

35:07.206 --> 35:09.238
OH, NO, NO, NO. THAT WAS
YOUR IDEA, NOT MINE.

35:09.238 --> 35:10.879
YOU DID WHAT YOU DID TO SAVE
YOURSELF AS MUCH AS ME.

35:10.879 --> 35:13.742
A COMPROMISE I'M REMINDED OF
EVERY DAY.

35:13.742 --> 35:16.685
YOU GOTPLENTY
 IN THE BARGAIN.

35:16.685 --> 35:18.747
OH... (inhales sharply)

35:24.753 --> 35:26.225
(chuckles)

35:26.225 --> 35:29.258
THESE GUYS REALLY PUT THE "SUCK"
IN SEERSUCKER.

35:29.258 --> 35:31.530
WANT TO BUMP IT UP
A NOTCH?

35:31.530 --> 35:32.761
WHAT A WASTE OF HUMANITY.

35:32.761 --> 35:34.463
OH, MY GOD.
 (cell phone rings and buzzes)

35:34.463 --> 35:36.205
(laughs)
 I'M SO SORRY.

35:36.205 --> 35:37.706
GOD, I'M SUCH AN IDIOT.

35:37.706 --> 35:39.868
NO, DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.
(speaking indistinctly)

35:39.868 --> 35:42.541
WITH WHOM DO I HAVE
THE PLEASURE OF SPEAKING?
 Hey.

35:42.541 --> 35:43.842
IT'S, UH...

35:43.842 --> 35:45.414
IT'S JACK PORTER.

35:45.414 --> 35:47.716
Listen, if you still
want to buy my boat,

35:47.716 --> 35:49.878
BRING A CHECK DOWN TO THE DOCKS
FIRST THING IN THE MORNING.

35:49.878 --> 35:51.280
Okay?

35:51.280 --> 35:52.781
THERE'S NOTHING
I'D LIKE TO DO MORE.

35:52.781 --> 35:54.323
All right.
See you then.

35:56.685 --> 35:58.927
(sighs)

36:00.389 --> 36:02.831
(cell phone beeps)

36:02.831 --> 36:05.864
♪♪♪

36:17.906 --> 36:21.350
(chuckles)

36:23.412 --> 36:27.316
(wind chimes tinkling)

36:37.326 --> 36:39.828
WELCOME HOME, AMANDA.

36:41.700 --> 36:43.702
I NEARLY DIDN'T
RECOGNIZE YOU TODAY,

36:43.702 --> 36:46.835
BUT THAT'S THE WHOLE POINT,
ISN'T IT?

36:46.835 --> 36:49.578
OH! UGH! UHH!

36:49.578 --> 36:51.640
DO YOU KNOW HOW EASY IT WOULD BE
FOR ME TO CRUSH YOUR WINDPIPE?

36:51.640 --> 36:53.982
I DON'T THINK
YOUR FATHER WOULD APPROVE.

36:53.982 --> 36:55.584
(chokes) AMANDA...

36:55.584 --> 36:57.916
OH...
YOUR FATHER TRUSTED ME.

36:57.916 --> 36:59.448
MY FATHER TRUSTED EVERYBODY.

36:59.448 --> 37:01.820
UGH!
 WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE, NOLAN?

37:01.820 --> 37:03.822
DON'T WORRY. DON'T WORRY.
YOUR SECRET'S SAFE.

37:03.822 --> 37:06.255
NO ONE WANTS
THIS IMPERIOUS CADRE

37:06.255 --> 37:08.457
OF TOXIC PHONIES TO EAT IT
MORE THAN YOURS TRULY.

37:08.457 --> 37:09.798
SO HOW CAN I BE OF SERVICE?

37:09.798 --> 37:10.929
YOU CAN'T.

37:10.929 --> 37:12.831
YOU'RE NOT A PART OF THIS.

37:12.831 --> 37:14.363
YES, I AM.

37:14.363 --> 37:15.904
REMEMBER,
I WITNESSED FIRSTHAND

37:15.904 --> 37:18.006
WHAT THESE PEOPLE DID
TO YOUR FATHER.

37:18.006 --> 37:18.967
THEY'RE HARD-CORE.

37:18.967 --> 37:20.669
I CAN HANDLE THEM.

37:20.669 --> 37:21.840
AND I HAVE NO PROBLEM
TAKING YOU DOWN, TOO,

37:21.840 --> 37:23.442
IF YOU GET IN MY WAY.

37:23.442 --> 37:25.013
I-I DON'T WANT
TO GET IN YOUR WAY.

37:25.013 --> 37:26.845
I WANT TO HELP YOU.

37:26.845 --> 37:28.947
YOU CAN'T HELP ME, NOLAN.

37:28.947 --> 37:31.620
(sighs)
SUIT YOURSELF.

37:31.620 --> 37:34.022
BUT I CAN BE
JUST AS POWERFUL AN ENEMY

37:34.022 --> 37:36.485
AS ANY ONE OF THEM.

37:36.485 --> 37:37.856
JUST SAYIN'.

37:37.856 --> 37:39.888
(wind chimes tinkling)

37:39.888 --> 37:41.560
OH...

37:41.560 --> 37:43.332
YOU MIGHT BE INTERESTED
TO KNOW,

37:43.332 --> 37:47.966
I HAD A NICE CHAT
WITH JACK PORTER TONIGHT.

37:47.966 --> 37:49.968
GUESS WHO'S STILL
CARRYING A TORCH

37:49.968 --> 37:52.040
FOR LITTLE AMANDA CLARKE.

37:52.040 --> 37:55.574
AMANDA CLARKE
NO LONGER EXISTS.

37:55.574 --> 37:57.906
(Angus & Julia Stone's
"For You" playing)

37:57.906 --> 38:00.479
♪ IF I TALK REAL SLOW ♪

38:00.479 --> 38:01.810
(metal door clatters)

38:01.810 --> 38:03.812
(man)
CLARKE, HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

38:03.812 --> 38:05.053
YOU'VE BEEN EMANCIPATED.

38:05.053 --> 38:08.887
♪ IF I TRY REAL HARD ♪

38:10.058 --> 38:11.660
(door bangs)

38:11.660 --> 38:12.791
♪ TO MAKE MY POINT ♪

38:12.791 --> 38:13.962
(buzzer sounds)

38:13.962 --> 38:14.923
♪ DEAR ♪

38:14.923 --> 38:16.665
(gate squeaks)

38:16.665 --> 38:17.996
♪ THAT YOU ♪

38:17.996 --> 38:20.499
♪ HAVE MY HEART ♪

38:20.499 --> 38:21.930
(tires screech)

38:21.930 --> 38:23.972
♪ HERE ♪

38:23.972 --> 38:25.404
♪ I ♪

38:25.404 --> 38:27.035
♪ GO ♪

38:27.035 --> 38:28.036
(brakes squeal)

38:28.036 --> 38:29.738
♪ I'LL TELL YOU ♪

38:29.738 --> 38:32.411
♪ WHAT YOU ALREADY KNOW ♪

38:32.411 --> 38:34.443
AMANDA CLARKE.

38:34.443 --> 38:35.944
WHO ARE YOU?

38:35.944 --> 38:38.917
NOLAN ROSS.
FRIEND OF YOUR FATHER'S.

38:38.917 --> 38:41.089
YOU'RE NOT EXACTLY
THE LITTLE ANGEL HE DESCRIBED.

38:41.089 --> 38:42.791
♪ I'LL TELL YOU ♪

38:42.791 --> 38:44.993
MY FATHER HASN'T SEEN ME
IN TEN YEARS.

38:44.993 --> 38:46.495
♪ ...KNOW ♪

38:46.495 --> 38:47.996
♪ IF YOU LOVE... ♪

38:47.996 --> 38:50.599
I'M SORRY TO BE
THE ONE TO TELL YOU.

38:50.599 --> 38:52.601
HE PASSED AWAY...

38:52.601 --> 38:54.533
SIX WEEKS AGO.

38:54.533 --> 38:57.105
♪ ...HEART ♪

38:57.105 --> 38:59.868
HE WANTED YOU
TO HAVE SOMETHING.

38:59.868 --> 39:02.070
WHATEVER THAT IS,
I DON'T WANT IT.

39:02.070 --> 39:04.843
OH, NO, NO, NO, TRUST ME.
YOU DEFINITELY DO.

39:04.843 --> 39:07.676
MY FATHER WAS A MURDERER
AND A LIAR.

39:07.676 --> 39:10.018
SO WHY WOULD I TRUST YOU,
HUH?

39:10.018 --> 39:12.681
'CAUSE THAT'S JUST WHAT
THEY WANT YOU TO BELIEVE.

39:12.681 --> 39:14.623
FORGET EVERYTHING THAT
YOU THINK YOU KNOW, AMANDA.

39:14.623 --> 39:16.084
YOUR DAD WAS PROTECTING YOU.

39:16.084 --> 39:17.686
FROM WHAT?

39:17.686 --> 39:19.688
OPEN THE BOX.

39:19.688 --> 39:21.830
FIND OUT.

39:21.830 --> 39:24.833
♪♪♪

39:28.737 --> 39:32.140
YOUR FATHER WAS THE FIRST PERSON
TO BELIEVE IN ME.

39:32.140 --> 39:34.743
HE INVESTED IN MY COMPANY
WHEN NO ONE ELSE WOULD.

39:34.743 --> 39:39.878
THAT KEY, IT OPENS
A LOCK BOX IN ZURICH.

39:39.878 --> 39:41.379
NOW THAT YOU'RE 18,

39:41.379 --> 39:44.983
YOU'RE OFFICIALLY 49% OWNER
OF MY COMPANY.

39:44.983 --> 39:48.056
BOARD MEETINGS ARE
EVERY OTHER WEDNESDAY, BUT...

39:48.056 --> 39:50.158
YOU DON'T HAVE TO SHOW UP.

39:50.158 --> 39:51.990
I NEVER DO.

39:51.990 --> 39:53.992
(David's voice)
"MY DEAR AMANDA...

39:53.992 --> 39:55.694
"IF YOU'RE READING THIS,

39:55.694 --> 39:58.166
"THEN TWO THINGS
HAVE COME TO PASS,

39:58.166 --> 40:00.699
"I AM FINALLY ABLE
TO PROVIDE YOU THE LIFE

40:00.699 --> 40:03.972
"YOU WERE UNJUSTLY DENIED,

40:03.972 --> 40:05.474
"AND SADLY,
I WON'T BE ABLE

40:05.474 --> 40:08.707
"TO SHARE
THAT LIFE WITH YOU.

40:08.707 --> 40:10.909
"I HOPE THESE JOURNALS
PROVIDE ANSWERS

40:10.909 --> 40:13.081
"TO THE QUESTIONS YOU'VE HAD
ALL THESE YEARS.

40:13.081 --> 40:16.184
"I AM NOT THE MAN
THEY SAY I AM

40:16.184 --> 40:19.718
AND I DID NOT DO
THE THINGS THEY SAY I DID."

40:19.718 --> 40:21.189
♪♪♪

40:21.189 --> 40:24.793
"ALL I ASK IS THAT YOU PROMISE
TO DO THE ONE THING

40:24.793 --> 40:27.496
THAT'S BEEN SO HARD
FOR ME TO DO."

40:27.496 --> 40:29.027
♪♪♪

40:29.027 --> 40:30.699
"FORGIVE."

40:32.130 --> 40:34.132
(Emily)
BUT THAT WAS A PROMISE

40:34.132 --> 40:35.834
I COULDN'T KEEP.

40:35.834 --> 40:37.135
(latch clicks)

40:37.135 --> 40:39.638
WHEN DECEPTION CUTS THIS DEEP,

40:39.638 --> 40:43.141
SOMEONE HAS TO PAY.

40:43.141 --> 40:44.643
MY FATHER'S CHANCE

40:44.643 --> 40:46.645
TO BRING JUSTICE
TO THE TRULY GUILTY

40:46.645 --> 40:49.217
WAS STOLEN FROM HIM.

40:49.217 --> 40:53.081
HIS ONLY OPTION
WAS TO FORGIVE.

40:53.081 --> 40:54.923
I HAVE OTHERS.

40:54.923 --> 40:58.627
♪♪♪

40:58.627 --> 41:00.889
WOULD YOU SET IT UP
BY THE WINDOWS, PLEASE?

41:00.889 --> 41:02.761
(Lydia speaks indistinctly)

41:02.761 --> 41:06.034
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.
I WANT THE BEACH HOUSE.

41:06.034 --> 41:08.036
HE HASN'T EVEN BEEN OUT...

41:08.036 --> 41:10.939
AND I'D LIKE SOME, UH,
PEPPER IN MY BISQUE.

41:10.939 --> 41:13.201
THEY SAY VENGEANCE
IS A DISH...
 (knocks on door)

41:13.201 --> 41:15.173
BEST SERVED COLD.

41:15.173 --> 41:18.607
BUT SOMETIMES IT'S AS WARM
AS A BOWL OF SOUP.

41:18.607 --> 41:20.108
♪ ...ALREADY KNOW ♪

41:20.108 --> 41:21.550
(lid clinks)

41:21.550 --> 41:23.251
MY FATHER...

41:23.251 --> 41:25.554
DIED AN INNOCENT MAN,

41:25.554 --> 41:28.116
BETRAYED BY THE WOMAN
HE LOVED.

41:28.116 --> 41:29.958
♪ I'LL TELL YOU ♪

41:29.958 --> 41:33.592
♪ WHAT YOU ALREADY KNOW ♪

41:33.592 --> 41:38.667
♪ IF YOU LOVE ME ♪

41:38.667 --> 41:41.930
♪ WITH ALL OF YOUR HEART ♪

41:41.930 --> 41:43.231
WHEN EVERYTHING YOU LOVE

41:43.231 --> 41:46.104
HAS BEEN STOLEN FROM YOU...

41:46.104 --> 41:50.278
SOMETIMES ALL YOU HAVE LEFT
IS REVENGE.

41:50.278 --> 41:51.810
LIKE I SAID...

41:51.810 --> 41:53.111
♪ I'LL MAKE YOU A STAR ♪

41:53.111 --> 41:56.244
THIS ISNOTA STORY
ABOUT FORGIVENESS.

41:56.244 --> 41:58.647
(phone rings)

41:58.647 --> 42:00.188
(rings, line clicks)

42:00.188 --> 42:01.519
(man) Yes?

42:01.519 --> 42:03.692
I WANT YOU TO FIND OUT
EVERYTHING YOU CAN

42:03.692 --> 42:06.555
ABOUT A YOUNG WOMAN
NAMED EMILY THORNE.

42:06.555 --> 42:08.156
Emily Thorne?

42:08.156 --> 42:09.858
THAT'S RIGHT.

42:09.858 --> 42:12.230
(line disconnects)

42:12.230 --> 42:14.162
♪ SHINING YOUR LIGHT ♪

42:14.162 --> 42:17.966
♪ MY WAY ♪
